# Portfolio Project Documentation

## Project Overview
Astro-based portfolio with multiple layout variations and content collections. Key features:
- 2/3-column masonry layouts <mcsymbol name="portfolio-3-col-masonry" filename="portfolio-3-col-masonry.astro" path="src/components/Cv/portfolio-3-col-masonry.astro" startline="1" type="component"></mcsymbol>
- Animated stats counter <mcsymbol name="heroCounter" filename="heroCounter.astro" path="src/components/heroCounter.astro" startline="1" type="component"></mcsymbol>
- MDX content management <mcfolder name="content" path="src/content/"></mcfolder>
- Responsive design for all device sizes
- Multiple portfolio layout options (2-column, 3-column, masonry)
- Dynamic content loading from MDX collections

### Technologies Used
- **Framework**: Astro with Preact integration
- **Styling**: CSS/SCSS with responsive design principles
- **Content**: MDX for portfolio items and blog posts
- **Animations**: Custom JavaScript animations for counters and transitions

### Target Audience
Professional developers and designers looking to showcase their work in a clean, customizable portfolio format.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Node.js (v16 or later)
- npm or yarn

### Installation
```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/portfolio.git

# Navigate to project directory
cd portfolio

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Start development server
npm run dev
```

